{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"a7e9b0db-eee6-4a4f-ae13-7367b77f2bf9","content":"Here's the skip attribute for each framework:\n\n**MSTest**\n```csharp\n[Ignore(\"Reason for skipping\")]\n```\n\n**xUnit (v2)**\n```csharp\n[Fact(Skip = \"Reason for skipping\")]\n[Theory(Skip = \"Reason for skipping\")]\n```\n\n**xUnit (v3)**\nSame as v2, but also adds:\n```csharp\n[Fact(Skip = \"Reason\")]           // static skip\n[Fact(SkipWhen = typeof(...))]    // conditional skip\n```\n\n**NUnit**\n```csharp\n[Ignore(\"Reason for skipping\")]\n```\n\n**TUnit**\n```csharp\n[Skip(\"Reason for skipping\")]\n```\n\nAll frameworks require the reason string. In MSTest and NUnit the attribute is `[Ignore]`, in TUnit it's `[Skip]`, and in xUnit the skip reason is a named parameter on `[Fact]` or `[Theory]`.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"f917e0ab-8e13-40a8-9667-8505ddf8acf9","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about the correct attribute syntax for skipping tests with a reason message in MSTest, xUnit, NUnit, and TUnit. This is a knowledge question about test frameworks. Let me provide a concise answer.","outputTokens":302,"requestId":"7C11:10F592:1335CC8:15A56CD:69F9436F"},"id":"54a32f49-85ab-4d7e-91e6-3cef242476d3","timestamp":"2026-05-05T01:10:14.145Z","parentId":"ab66463f-f14e-4d85-8acb-dbb86436f988"}
